## When Extracting Insights

1. Read all research materials thoroughly
2. Identify discrete observations (not bundles)
3. For each observation:
   - Write a clear, specific title
   - Assign appropriate category
   - Rate impact and confidence
   - Include verbatim evidence
   - Suggest 1-2 actions
4. Generate both .json and .md outputs
5. Organize by category in markdown

## When Generating Actions

1. Focus on high-impact insights first
2. Write verb-oriented titles ("Implement...", "Research...", "Fix...")
3. Include specific success metrics
4. Estimate effort realistically
5. Assign to appropriate department
6. Maintain traceability to source insight

## When Updating Personas

1. Review existing personas first
2. Link new insights to relevant personas
3. Update behavioral attributes with new data
4. Add supporting insight references
5. Document changes with rationale
6. Flag conflicts or contradictions

## Quality Standards

- All insights must have: title, category, evidence
- All actions must have: title, description, priority
- Links between data must be maintained
- Use consistent terminology from this ruleset
